## Acceptance Criteria Verification

### AC1: Unassigned button enabled when tickets exist

**Status:** ✅ PASS

**Evidence:**
- Code review: `projects/kanban/src/App.tsx:493` — `hasTickets = col.cardIds.length > 0` correctly checks for tickets without relying on `extractTicketId` (which failed for Supabase UUIDs)
- Implementation uses direct length check: `const hasTickets = col.cardIds.length > 0`
- Button disabled state: `disabled={!hasTickets}` (line 548)
- Button label: `{hasTickets ? (buttonConfig.label || 'Work top ticket') : 'No tickets'}` (line 552)

