## Evidence

### Code Review

**Status:** ✅ PASS

**Findings:**
- Root cause identified: `extractTicketId` only matched numeric IDs and returned `null` for Supabase UUIDs, causing `hasTickets` to be `false` even when tickets existed
- Fix implemented: Changed to check `col.cardIds.length > 0` directly, which works for both numeric IDs and UUIDs
- Code locations verified:
  - `projects/kanban/src/App.tsx:493` — `hasTickets` calculation
  - `projects/kanban/src/App.tsx:548` — Button disabled state
  - `projects/kanban/src/App.tsx:552` — Button label rendering
- Compliance with requirements: Yes — all acceptance criteria addressed by root cause fix
- Code quality: Good — follows existing patterns, proper TypeScript types, includes accessibility attributes

### Build Verification

**Status:** ✅ PASS

**Command:** `npm run build`

**Result:**
- Build completed successfully
- TypeScript errors: None
- Linter errors: None
- All type checks passed

